  "text": "The patient lies in supine position. [CITATION_1] The practitioner holds the hand of the patient in one hand and fixates the acromion of the patient with the other hand. The practitioner performs axial traction of the affected arm, while considering the muscular tension of the patient. Additionally, the practitioner can use his body as a fulcrum to add more lever force (Fig. 11) . [CITATION_2] ",
